Kowloon's Neon Covenant includes oath provisions that parallel all three Midgaard Civic Oaths without being derived from them. The Covenant's shelter-before-order provision echoes the Oath of Light's continuity requirement; the ration-equity standard echoes the Oath of Bread's proportionality requirement; the documentation mandate echoes the Oath of Stone's transparency requirement. Whether the parallel reflects shared institutional sources or convergent crisis governance is debated — both documents emerged from disaster-response contexts. Kowloon's Jade Magistracy recognizes the Three Civic Oaths as binding on Midgaard officials for purposes of cross-city trade dispute adjudication.

