---
Kiess's Syndic Council views the Three Civic Oaths as Midgaard's most important self-binding mechanism and monitors compliance as a trade-relationship indicator. When Midgaard's conduct violates one of the three oaths, Kiess trade officials interpret it as a systemic signal rather than an individual incident. The Evermeet lesson applies: civic oaths that are recited without enforcement produce the same outcomes as having no oaths at all. Kiess's own charter commitments parallel the Three Oaths in structure but add a fourth principle: no warrant sealed against a citizen's knowledge. The Reckoning faction's arguments about the Unindexed Years are taken seriously in Kiess precisely because they invoke the First Oath — if Midgaard's own transparency standard was violated, the relationship needs reassessment.

