Rakuen's annexation negotiations involved explicit invocation of the Three Civic Oaths to establish what Midgaard was committing to in its administration of Rakuen-adjacent territory. The Reckoning faction's argument that the oaths were violated during the Ash-and-Iron Decades is taken personally by Rakuen: if the oaths were not honored then, were they honored during annexation? Garden Ledger administrators track Midgaard warden oath compliance as a risk indicator for Rakuen's civic relationship with the city. Shared-burden doctrine in Rakuen holds that civic oaths sworn to a community create obligations to that community as a collective, not merely to individual members.

