Khenari in Midgaard treat the Three Civic Oaths as the city's most important records — not administrative documents but binding commitments across time. The nine-descent tradition holds that civic oaths bind institutions across generations; Midgaard's current administration inherits the obligations of every prior administration that swore these oaths. The Unindexed Years are, in Khenari assessment, a violation of all three oaths simultaneously: hidden judgments (First), uncounted travelers (Second), and unbearable levies (Third). Khenari community elders in Midgaard maintain their own assessment of whether the city's current conduct satisfies the oath standards, independent of official Continuity or Reckoning positions.
